token_lists.title: My reflections
token_lists.description:
My reflection isn't always perfect, but it is always sublime- mostly, I see the dark and rotten, the flesh bleeding, our earth screaming to survive. So much to fix, so few glimpses of hope from the divine.


My reflection tells a story, I listen and I watch - with eyes renewed from psychedelics, I look for pieces we forgot, something to take out, change, add…an incredible puzzle piece that makes you see it all in a new light. The thing to wipe your ego - the thing to set you free, to stop the blood from gushing, to finally make your numb heart fucking FEEL. 

I've been wiping blood and cleaning wounds my entire life. I guess I just embrace it now.

token_lists.title: Vessels Crew Colony-Alpha
token_lists.description:
We are the Crew Colony-Alpha
Searching for the explorers of legend known as the crew “Dutch”.

I am Captain Laedyn from the planet Solonas. My planet was dying from pollution, and we were running out of water, I was sent with my crew to find other life and resources to save my planet. Two years into my mission we were boarded by pirates, we fought with everything we had but I lost my crew before I could kill the last one.

I thought all was lost, I was alone but determined to complete my mission I never gave up.  After three years of solitude and on the brink of insanity, the only thing that kept me sane was the "bear monster" that my little girl gave me to keep me safe.  I spotted another ship in the distance. I received a message of peace and at this point what did I have to lose!

I boarded the ship only to discover that my situation was not so unique.  I was greeted by Captain Sullyeroth, who through a translator described their situation.  He was from a planet that I couldn’t pronounce, he also was trying to save his planet. He came across two explorers whose ancestors were from the planet Earth, Martinez and Doobie along with his original crew member Estrada.

We decided to join forces and become a crew of five, leaving my failing ship behind.  We heard of the Crew Dutch and hope to find them, they are known experts in exploration and survival.  Together we can find the resources and technology to hopefully save more than one planet.  It turns out that there is life everywhere in the Universe and so few appreciate how fragile it is. We hope to create a colony and prove sustainable life is possible and bring people from our dying planets to the colony.

token_lists.title: The South Bay Prowlers
token_lists.description:
The South Bay Prowlers are signing up with YANGWONG for a bit of wet work and turf warfare. These young toughs are already making a name for themselves in the colony’s underbelly, making moves left and right trying to get the attention of one of the established gangs. The Prowlers have adopted the symbol of the tiger; led by the mercurial Ayu and his truffle pig, Harvey, the Prowlers initiates wear jackets emblazoned with the symbol of their leader’s mask. 

Recikil is the group’s muscle; his fins and horns enable him to effectively fight both on land and in water. Ayu found Reckikil one day down at the docks, surrounded by fallen ruffians, with his eyes pulsating with an intense white light. Ayu knew immediately that he must be attuning to the magical energies of the planet and quickly recruited him.

Neal and Ledios are siblings with an affinity for tech - together they conduct surveillance on potential targets and dismantle any security systems that stand in their way. Their hi-tech visors indicate they might not have the most humble beginnings, but Ayu knew that it wouldn’t hurt to have a few aristocrats in his midst should they ever get in trouble with the royal guards. Ledios took immediately to Ayu, immediately getting a tattoo to match her leader’s. Neal, on the other hand, was fascinated by Recikil’s fins and fashioned a bioengineered one for herself that shifts to match the color of her visor.

Aguirre is the smooth talker of the bunch, putting on a charming face in order to collect intel and create distractions. Where muscle or technology fail, charisma prevails. She looks innocent, but that’s only to distract you from the knife Ayu is drawing from his cloak.

Together, the Prowlers have set up quite a name for themselves. The tiger symbol has caught on among the colony’s youth and many fancy themselves roustabouts by wearing their colors. But only these 5 have drawn the eye of the Mapleborough Royals and Sneak Thieves. 

The Prowlers don’t know it yet, but this next job is more of an audition. They are set up to fail, but how they wriggle into and out of the trouble that awaits them will go a long way in the eyes of the colony’s kingpins.

token_lists.title: Vessels Crew Challenge- Crew Gaia
token_lists.description:
The Landers come from a ruined world.  They witnessed corporate greed win out against the pleading of a dying Earth.  When the earth finally gave in, they fled like rats.

Now they've begun the cycle again.  Pollution pours out of our colony at alarming rates like a raging river as the Landers struggle to convert new natural resources into revenue streams.  

This planet has already begun to fight back.  Many have heard the wails and haunting songs of the Deep Ones.   There are whispers of changes happening in the woods.  And the local wildlife have already learned to stay clear of our colonial activities.  

Someone must defend this planet's natural beauty before the ways of Earth destroy it.  Someone must take a stand against Landers putting themselves before this world and it's future.   We are that someone.  We are Crew Gaia.

Brooks is our leader, planning the missions we take and the core of our team.  We like to joke that we rally at the sound of her mighty roar for ecojustice.  

Morolia covers recon and intelligence assisted by her Omni Nibbler.  Her sharp eyes catch every detail.  She is definitely the best scout born on our new home.  

Koa (or Foxy Mama to the local roughnecks) is supposed to be our intelligence officer, analyzing the reports Morolia sends her when she's not boozing it up at the Fisherman's Robot.  She's got a clever way of looking at things and her tongue has a bite that keeps most brutes in line.  Often accused of being too promiscuous by colony elders, she is known to reply "I just have a ferocious appetite."

When things call for a swift hand and a light touch, it's time for Light Fire to do her thing.  Whether we need something acquired or an "obstacle" "removed", Light Fire has a way if getting the job done without raising any alarms.  She's the tip of our spear, and how we usually like to handle any confrontation our mouths can't take care of.  She doesn't mind, which is why we all sleep behind locked doors. She doesn't mind that either, as locks mean very little to her.

And finally there is me, Alder!  I can't claim to be brave, or smart, or deadly... but I also can't just sit around and watch our new home be slowly destroyed.  There is so much beauty to be discovered and studied.  So I support the crew by making sure wherever we go in home.  I'm a people person and maintain our connection with local vendors to keep us well supplied and informed on who may or may not be looking for us to ask about a recent "accident" at a supposed lumber mill.  I try to be the glue that seeps into the cracks to fill the gaps in our team and bind it together.  Brooks tells me that each of us count in the battle for our new world.  So I'm doing my part, however I can.
